In this proclamation, President Donald J. Trump declares May 2017 as Older Americans Month. He highlights the importance of older Americans as the nation's memory and acknowledges their contributions to the country. The president also emphasizes the advancements in medical technology that allow older people to remain healthy and active. He encourages seniors to make a difference in their communities by sharing their talents and time. Additionally, President Trump commits to ensuring that older Americans receive the care and support they need. He calls upon all Americans to honor and care for their elders throughout the year.